ued value. The same accrued balance remains claimable on repeated calls.","impact":"Any account with non-zero accrued rewards can repeatedly claim and drain LEND held by the router, including rewards attributable to other users.","paths":["User accrues positive `lendAccrued` once","User calls `claimLend` and receives full accrued amount","`lendAccrued[user]` is unchanged","User repeats claims until router LEND balance is exhausted"],"round":3,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-015","severity":"High","confidence":"medium","title":"Liquidity checks accept zero oracle prices, creating fail-open borrow authorization","locations":["LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:431","LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:445","LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:460","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:152","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:617"],"claim":"`getHypotheticalAccountLiquidityCollateral` uses oracle prices without validating `price > 0`. If a market price returns `0`, borrow-side effects for that asset become `0`, and collateral checks can pass despite real economic risk.","impact":"During oracle outages/misconfiguration returning zero, users can borrow assets with effectively no borrow value added in checks, potentially extracting pool liquidity and creating bad debt.","paths":["Oracle returns 0 price for borrow market","User calls same-chain or cross-chain borrow","Borrow value contribution is computed as zero in liquidity check","Borrow proceeds while true collateralization is insufficient"],"round":3,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-016","severity":"Medium","confidence":"low","title":"Borrow/redeem update accounting after external calls, leaving reentrancy window for callback-capable tokens","locations":["LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:121","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:124","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:127","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:167","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:170","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:179"],"claim":"`redeem` and `borrow` perform external protocol/token calls before updating internal accounting (`totalInve